arChildNodes.szComment: Eru sits by the guardian and lays his hand on top of the spirit. He strokes it. Eru closes his eyes, fighting off tears.

THE PLAYER crouches down beside him. Eru opens his eyes and lifts his hand, watching the ooze of corruption drip from his fingers. 
He puts his hand back on the guardian, not taking his gaze off it. The Player lifts Makaâ€™s dagger, ready to stab it into the guardian. 
Before they can strike, Eru holds out his hand to stop them.
The Player lowers their arm and holds the knife handle towards Eru. He takes the knife. He closes his eyes.

Pronounced: 
ah ooo anna ahk say pay

Eru plunges the knife into the guardianâ€™s chest. Corruption and blood spurts out of the chest and gushes onto the floor. 
Eru starts to sing a song in his native language, low and mournful. 

Pronounced: 
naha-naan see nahm nahn

His face contorts, and tears brim in his eyes. He digs into the body with the sound of meat tearing, and bones crunching.  

Pronounced: 
pah nah oh-nook weh

Pronounced:
ah boo-lahn lay sick woo kiss-ehss

A sickening snap. Eru stops singing. Slowly, he pulls out the heart and takes out a ceremonial cloth.  
Eru holds the cloth out to the player.  The Player takes the cloth and opens it. Eru carefully lays the heart in the cloth, his hands and arms covered in blood and corruption.
The Player stands up, folding up the heart in the cloth. Eru turns back to the guardian and closes its eyes.
